textAfterTable: September 7, 2010 - 7:53am -- braswell POPLARVILLE - Two veterans of the industry have been named to oversee food service at Pearl River Community College.Todd Hickman of Petal is the new food service manager and Leah Woodard of Picayune is assistant manager. Valley, a Jackson-based company, operates Pearl River''s dining hall and the Bistro grill.The pair doesn''t plan any major changes."We hope to improve overall customer satisfaction and the image food service has on campus," Hickman said.He describes the job with Valley as a good fit for him and his family."It was an extremely good opportunity to work with a large company but be in a situation where it''s in a small town in Mississippi," he said.
